de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.concepts

Interface AdditivelyInvertible<NumberConcept>

  • Type Parameters:
    NumberConcept - A reference to the Class or Interface which the inverse element will be a type of.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Invertible<NumberConcept>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabeledMatrix<LabelType>, Matrix, Ring<RingType>, Vector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Interval, LabeledRegularMatrix, LabeledSymmetricMatrix, RegularMatrix, RegularVector, Scalar, SquareMatrix, SymmetricMatrix, Vector2D, Vector3D

    public interface AdditivelyInvertible<NumberConcept>
extends Invertible<NumberConcept>
    The "additive inversion" operation can be any unary operation that returns the "opposite" of this Object.

    The additive inverse of a number and the number itself combined with an additive operation yield the additively neutral element called "Zero Element".

    See Also:
    Wikipedia: Additive inverse
